				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Kreuz und Quer durch das Neue Testament" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>This game is a mixturure of a Bible trivia Game and Monopoly.&amp;#10;The board game has 2 parts: In the middle a card of Mediterranean Sea at the period of Jesus. There is a single path through this map.&amp;#10;The second part of the board are fields at the border of the board with fields known from Monopoly. Instead of streets this are chapters from the New Testament. There are some special fields where you have to ask questions from the bible.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game starts at the start point of the map track. The actual player roles 2 die and moves. dependent of the points on the die he gets questions from different stacks of cards (all from the bible). If he knows the answer he gets the points written on the card.    &amp;#10;When the track ends the figure changes to the Monopoly kind path. Like in Monopoly you can by the fields, but not with money but with the points you have collected with the right answered questions. You have to pay parking fee for fields owned by other players. As in Monopoly you can increase the parking fee by placing houses (they are named red and white stones here.&amp;#10;Running out of points and area cards you may change back to the Mediterranean Sea path 1 time to get points answering new questions.&amp;#10;The game ends after a predefined time. The player with the most points wins (including value of area cards and stones).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Variants (mentioned in rules):&amp;#10;1. Just role the die and run first the Mediterranean Sea path and after that the Monopoly path. The first player who comes to the Start of teh Monopoly Path again.  &amp;#10;2. Bible trivia: Just use the question cards. Who has the most points at a predefined time wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
